crowdsourced_ai_results.analysis: The sample is a Rust-based backdoor that collects system information (username, platform, boottime, architecture) and communicates with a Command and Control (C2) server. It establishes an insecure WebSocket connection to `web.commoncome.online:8080` to exfiltrate the collected data and likely receive commands to execute on the compromised system, as indicated by its process creation capabilities (`fork`, `execvp`).
